publicDescription.summary: Casa Feliz, translated as ‘Happy House’, is situated in the peaceful village of Skirlaugh, near Kingston upon Hull, Beverley, Hornsea and Bridlington so the location is ideal for exploring both coast and country. This property is very comfortable with all the facilities provided for a relaxing break, including the added bonus of a hot tub. The property features an open plan living and kitchen area, four bedrooms and a private garden, it's the ideal home to enjoy with your loved ones.
publicDescription.space:
Casa Feliz is an extensive home perfect for group getaways, whether that be family retreats or a social get-together. There are four bedrooms; two doubles, one small double, and one king, along with a large family bathroom. The king room spans the full space on the second floor and boasts a modern ensuite shower room. 

Two of the first-floor bedrooms have ensuites - perfect for additional privacy when staying as a large group. 

On the ground floor there is a large open plan living, kitchen and dining room, modernly designed with luxury interiors. This is the perfect space for all guests to enjoy home cooked meals around the dining table, or casual dining whilst enjoying the beautifully curated interiors.

The groud floor is also home to a separate smaller living room, and a downstairs WC. 

Outside is an expansive garden, expertly designed and preseted to include furniture for lounging or dining al-fresco, outdoor cooking facilities and a rare find with such a beautiful property; a hot tub, which can be enjoyed all year round.  

Host & Stay are committed to our owners that their homes are protected during guest bookings. For this reason, we require all our guests to transfer a Damage Deposit (refundable, subject to an administration charge) or, to purchase an Accidental Damage Waiver which will cover you for up to £500.00 of accidental damage during your stay.
publicDescription.access:
Guests have access to the full property. The keys to Casa Feliz are accessed via a key safe box and full details will be accessed prior to check in. 

Private on-site parking is available for up to five vehicles.
publicDescription.neighborhood:
Skirlaugh is located around seven miles North East of Kingston upon Hull City Centre.  

Hull is a maritime city next to the Humber estuary in the East Riding of Yorkshire. The city is a treasure trove of rich seafaring history, stunning architecture, and a thriving arts scene. From exploring the captivating museums and art galleries to strolling around the picturesque marina, Hull offers a unique blend of cultural experiences and leisure activities. 

Over the last few years, Hull has transformed itself into a real gem in Yorkshire’s crown offering the perfect mix of museums, shopping and nightlife.

You’ll find an abundance of galleries and museums around the city, while one of the main attractions in Hull is The Deep. This award-winning aquarium and be taken on a journey through prehistoric seas, past tropical lagoons, into the vast open oceans, down to the darkest depths, through the chilly Kingdom of ice and into the future.

Also nearby is the pretty market town of Beverley. A prominent feature is the historic and attractive place of worship, Beverley Minster. Visitors to Beverley often remark that it’s got a lot more to offer than had been expected. It’s an incredibly interesting, historic market town. Possessing it’s very own Minster and historic town centre, Beverley is a very pretty town which is full of wow factor for visitors.

Casa Feliz is close to Rise Hall, a popular wedding venue so the property also makes for the perfect base when visiting here for events.
publicDescription.transit:
The nearest train station to Skirlaugh can be found in Hull where you’ll find routes to Bridlington, Doncaster, Halifax, London, Manchester, Scarborough, Sheffield and York. 

A number of bus routes can be found running through Skirlaugh. Hop on the 24 to visit Hull and Hornsea, travel on the 242 for Hedon and Beverley, or take a trip on the 243 to enjoy Withernsea. 

The nearest airport is Humberside, 32 miles away from Skirlaugh. International visitors can also arrive by ferry into Hull.

publicDescription.summary: Nestled in the beautiful village of Beadnell on the Northumberland coastline, The Bach is a recently refurbished property with style in abundance. Aptly named, a ‘Bach’ is a cosy and modest holiday home. Pronounced ‘batch’, it was thought to be originally short for bachelor pad but actually often tended to be a family holiday home. Sleeping up to 4 guests, this bach is dog friendly and perfect for family staycations, romantic retreats and getaways with friends.
publicDescription.space:
Upon entering The Bach, you’ll be impressed with its bright and modern look. Recently renovated to the highest standard, the house boasts premium furniture and luxury interiors. Perfect for socialising, the ground floor has an open plan kitchen, living and dining room.

After a fun day at the beach, retreat to the living area with your loved ones for a cosy night in. Snuggle up on the sofa and turn on the flat screen TV to keep up with your favourite shows. Beautifully styled, the living area has a grey and mustard colour scheme with touches of tartan soft furnishings. 

The kitchen is ultra stylish with dark blue cabinets and marble worktops. Perfectly on trend, it also has white brick style tiles which complement the space beautifully. You’ll have everything you need for your self-catering stay as The Bach is fully equipped with an oven, hob, fridge, microwave, toaster and kettle. There are also the added luxuries of a washing machine, dryer and dishwasher. 

The dining area includes a modern white dining table with four dining chairs. Ideal for family meals and dining with friends, there is ample space for all of your party.

Head upstairs to the first floor and you’ll find two bedrooms and the family bathroom. The master bedroom boasts a king size bed with a comfy mattress and plush bedding. With crisp white walls and spotlights, this space is tranquil and modern. Pops of colour and luxury are added through teal coloured soft furnishings and beautiful wall prints.

Along the hallway is the second bedroom. Boasting the same high finish as the rest of the house, the room has comfortable twin beds with mustard blankets and cushions. A truly cosy space to relax, you’ll enjoy your sleep at The Bach.

Unique in style, the family bathroom has white tiled walls and a striking patterned, tiled floor. The space boasts a bath with an overhead shower, a vanity unit and a WC.

Outside you’ll find a fully enclosed garden with outdoor furniture. Ideal for al fresco dining and drinks in the sunshine, this is an added bonus with the property. Right on the water, you’ll have lovely views with the sound of the river passing by.

Host & Stay are committed to our owners that their homes are protected during guest bookings. For this reason, we require all our guests to transfer a Damage Deposit (refundable, subject to an administration charge) or, to purchase an Accidental Damage Waiver which will cover you for up to £500.00 of accidental damage during your stay.
publicDescription.access:
Guests have access to the full property. The keys to the property are accessed via a secure key safe and full details will be provided shortly before your arrival date.

There is one designated parking space for The Bach in the carpark as well as free on street parking.

The Bach is dog friendly and we welcome up to two small dogs or one large dog. We kindly ask that dogs are kept off the furniture and downstairs.
publicDescription.neighborhood:
The Bach is located in Beadnell - a charming village right on the Northumberland coast. Ideal for seaside stays, the village is set at the end of a stunning stretch of sandy shores. At the North end of the bay is the harbour and to the South you’ll find huge sand dunes which go on for miles. Gather all of the family together to enjoy the renowned watersports on offer. From surfing and sailing to scuba diving and bodyboarding, you won’t get bored of things to do at Beadnell Bay! 

If you want to get active during your stay, Beadnell is also ideal for walking as it boasts great routes along the coastline with unrivalled views. You can also relax at one of the many restaurants on offer. Just a short 5 minute walk from The Bach is the Craster Arms where you can enjoy a drink and food within a building which dates back to the 15th century.

Beadnell is just 4 miles from Bamburgh so you can easily explore other areas within Northumberland during your stay. Here you can head to England’s most northerly land-based lighthouse where there are incredible views of the Holy Island. You can also visit Bamburgh Castle, a striking Grade I listed building which has stood on the Northumberland coastline for over 1,400 years. Known as one of the finest castles in the country, there is a wealth of history to uncover during your visit.
publicDescription.transit:
The Bach is within walking distance of all that Beadnell has to offer. 

If you plan on visiting other towns and villages during your stay, hop on the Arriva X18 route which travels to Newcastle with stops in Amble and Alnwick amongst others.  

The nearest train station to Beadnell is at Chathill which is 3.7 miles away.

publicDescription.summary:
Nestled in the idyllic village of Lauenen, just a short drive from the world-renowned resort town of Gstaad, this luxurious 5-bedroom chalet offers an unparalleled Alpine retreat. With its perfect blend of traditional Swiss architecture and modern amenities, this property promises a serene yet sophisticated mountain living experience.

Key Features:
Location: Situated in the picturesque Lauenen Valley, the chalet boasts breathtaking, stunning views of the surrounding mountains and lush forests. The tranquil setting is ideal for those seeking privacy and a deep connection with nature, while still being close to the vibrant social scene and upscale amenities of Gstaad.

Architecture & Design:
• Exterior: The chalet's exterior showcases classic Swiss design elements, including wooden facades, pitched roofs, and expansive balconies that provide panoramic views of the stunning landscape.
• Interior: Step inside to discover a harmonious blend of rustic charm and contemporary elegance. High ceilings with exposed wooden beams, large windows, and stone accents create a warm and inviting atmosphere.
publicDescription.space:
Living Spaces:
• Living Room: The spacious living area features a cozy fireplace, perfect for gathering with family and friends after a day of exploring the mountains.
• Dining Area: Adjacent to the living room, the dining area offers ample space for hosting dinner parties, complemented by a large table and stylish lighting fixtures.
• Kitchen: The state-of-the-art kitchen is equipped with high-end appliances, custom cabinetry, and a generous island, making it a chef’s dream.

Bedrooms & Bathrooms:
• Master Suite: The chalet’s master suite is a sanctuary of comfort, featuring a king-size bed, private balcony, and an en-suite bathroom with a soaking tub and walk-in shower.
• Guest Rooms: Additional bedrooms are thoughtfully designed, each offering plush bedding, ample storage, and access to well-appointed bathrooms.
• Five Bedrooms: This luxurious chalet includes a total of five beautifully appointed bedrooms, ensuring ample space and privacy for all guests.

Wellness & Recreation:
• Fitness Room: Stay active with a fully equipped fitness room, ensuring you can maintain your workout routine even while on holiday.
Outdoor Spaces:
• Terraces & Balconies: Multiple terraces and balconies provide the perfect spots for outdoor dining, sunbathing, or simply soaking in the stunning views.
• Garden: The beautifully landscaped garden offers a tranquil retreat, with lush greenery and a charming patio area equipped with outdoor furniture for relaxing and entertaining.
• Outdoor Furniture: Enjoy the fresh mountain air in style and comfort with elegant outdoor furniture arranged to maximize your enjoyment of the stunning natural surroundings.

Additional Amenities:
• Ski Room: A dedicated ski room with storage and boot warmers ensures your equipment is ready for action.
• Garage: The chalet includes a spacious garage, providing secure parking for multiple vehicles.

All the Luxury Amenities: This exceptional property is outfitted with all the luxury amenities you could desire, ensuring a lavish and comfortable stay. From high-speed internet and advanced home automation systems to high-quality linens and personalized concierge services, every detail has been considered to provide an extraordinary living experience.

Experience the Ultimate Alpine Lifestyle:
Whether you are looking for a peaceful retreat or an active mountain adventure, this 5-bedroom chalet in Lauenen, Gstaad, provides the perfect base. Enjoy world-class skiing, hiking, and mountain biking in the stunning Bernese Oberland, and unwind in luxurious comfort at the end of each day.

This exceptional property is more than just a home; it’s a lifestyle. Embrace the beauty and tranquility of Swiss mountain living in a chalet that exudes charm, elegance, and modern luxury.
